        <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge provides disc stack centrifuge optimization expertise — including gravity disc sizing, flow rate calibration, and operating temperature tuning — to maximize separation quality on customer installations. These adjustments can increase effective centrifuge efficiency by 20–40% without hardware changes. Based in Warren, Michigan, Dolphin Centrifuge has over 40 years of experience optimizing industrial centrifuge performance.</p>
      </div>
      <!-- Intro with hero image -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <img src="/images/disc-stack-centrifuge-efficiency/disc-centrifuge-nomogram-825.webp" alt="Disc Centrifuge Efficiency Nomogram for gravity disc selection" width="825" height="550" loading="eager" class="rounded-lg w-full mb-6" />
        <p class="text-text leading-relaxed">Users of disc-stack centrifuges often ask about ways to increase the capacity or quality of the effluent from their centrifuge equipment. A handful of considerations have a big impact on centrifuge efficiency.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Table of Contents -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Table of Contents</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-navy">
